{{Infobox holiday |holiday_name = International Tiger Day |type = International |longtype = |image = Male Tiger Ranthambhore.jpg |official_name = |nickname = |duration = 1 day |frequency = annual |scheduling = same day each year |date = July 29 |celebrations = |observances = |relatedto = }}
'''''Global Tiger Day''''', often called '''International Tiger Day''', is an annual celebration to raise awareness for [[tiger]] conservation, held annually on 29 July.<ref>{{cite news|title=World's first tiger summit ends with £330m pledged amid lingering doubts|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2010/nov/24/tiger-summit-vladimir-putin|accessdate=1 September 2011 | location=London|work=The ..Guardian|first=Jonathan|last=Watts|date=24 November 2010}}</ref> It was created in 2010 at the [[Saint Petersburg]] Tiger Summit.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vietnam observes International Tiger Day|url=http://www.thanhniennews.com/2010/Pages/20110730132953.aspx|accessdate=1 September 2011}}</ref> The goal of the day is to promote a global system for protecting the natural [[habitat]]s of tigers and to raise public awareness and support for tiger conservation issues.<ref>{{cite web|title=International Tiger Conservation Forum|url=http://eng.tigecampanterforum2010.ru/|work=Tiger Conservation Forum|accessdate=1 September 2011}}{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
== By year == === 2017 === The seventh annual Global Tiger Day was celebrated in various ways around the world. Local events have been organized in Bangladesh, Nepal, and India as well as non-tiger-range countries such as England and the United States.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.theindependentbd.com/printversion/details/106312|title=Saving Our Tigers|last=Independent|first=The|work=Saving Our Tigers {{!}} theindependentbd.com|access-date=2017-07-29}}</ref><ref>[http://www.manoramaonline.com/environment/environment-news/2017/07/29/international-tiger-day.html International Tiger Day]</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/7th-world-tiger-day-to-be-marked-on-saturday/|title=7th World Tiger Day to be marked on Saturday|date=2017-07-27|work=The Himalayan Times|access-date=2017-07-29|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/Andhra-Pradesh/2017-07-29/Tiger-Day-to-be-held--at--Indira-Gandhi-Zoological-Park--today/315381|title=Tiger Day to be held at Indira Gandhi Zoological Park today|website=The Hans India|language=en|access-date=2017-07-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.itv.com/news/calendar/2017-07-26/yorkshire-wildlife-park-prepares-for-tiger-day/|title=Yorkshire Wildlife Park prepares for Tiger Day|work=ITV News|access-date=2017-07-29|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.oregonzoo.org/events/international-tiger-day|title=International Tiger Day|work=Oregon Zoo|access-date=2017-07-29|language=en}}</ref> Some celebrities also participated by removing their social media profile photos.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.good.is/articles/zachary-quinto-wants-to-save-the-tigers|title=‘Star Trek’ Actor Says Earth’s 4,000 Tigers Are Worth Saving|date=2017-07-17|work=GOOD Magazine|access-date=2017-07-29|language=en}}</ref> WWF continued its promotion of the "Double Tigers" campaign through investing in rangers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tigerday.panda.org/|title=WWF - Tiger Day|website=tigerday.panda.org|language=en|access-date=2017-07-29}}</ref> Several companies partnered with WWF to help raise awareness.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.home.eco/the-world-needs-more-tigers-13eb6e5eb394|title=The world needs more tigers – News {{!}} .eco|date=2017-07-28|work=News {{!}} .eco|access-date=2017-07-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://3890.tigerbeer.com|title=Age gate|website=3890.tigerbeer.com|language=us|access-date=2017-07-29}}</ref> === 2018 === More awareness in the entire world of tiger populations and the challenges for their conservationists. [[India]] counts the number of wild tigers every four year and show a promising rise from 1411 in 2006 to 2226 in 2014. According to WWF the world population in 2016 was ±3900. <ref>[https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/international-tiger-day-2018-on-international-tiger-day-hopes-pinned-for-tiger-population-to-increas-1891554 On International Tiger Day, Hopes Pinned For Tiger Population To Increase] Anuj Pant on NDTV, 29 July 2018</ref>
