[[File:Eaton's War Bonds Rally 1943 Audience.jpg|thumb|240px|Victory Bonds rally, 1943]]The '''National War Finance Committee''' was set up in [[Canada]] in December 1941 by the [[Department of Finance Canada|Department of Finance]]. It was initially chaired by [[George Wilbur Spinney]], president of the [[Bank of Montreal]], and later by [[Graham Towers]], the Governor of the [[Bank of Canada]]. The Committee was responsible for raising war financing through the sale of [[War bonds|Victory Bonds]]. Prior to the Committee's establishment, war financing was the responsibility of the Department of Finance.<ref>Jeff Keshen, ''Saints, Sinners, and Soldiers: Canada's Second World War'', Vancouver: UBC Press 2004, p. 32</ref>

