{{Infobox ethnic group |group = Uzbek Canadians |native_name = |native_name_lang = |population = '''2,725''' (by ancestry, <small>[[Canada 2011 Census|2011 Census]]</small>)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/nhs-enm/2011/dp-pd/dt-td/Rp-eng.cfm?TABID=2&LANG=E&APATH=3&DETAIL=0&DIM=0&FL=A&FREE=0&GC=0&GID=1118296&GK=0&GRP=0&PID=105396&PRID=0&PTYPE=105277&S=0&SHOWALL=0&SUB=0&Temporal=2013&THEME=95&VID=0&VNAMEE=&VNAMEF=&D1=0&D2=0&D3=0&D4=0&D5=0&D6=0 |title=2011 National Household Survey: Data tables |author=[[Statistics Canada]] |accessdate=11 February 2014}}</ref> |popplace = [[Ontario]] and [[Quebec]] |languages = [[Canadian English]]{{·}}[[Canadian French]]{{·}}[[Uzbek language|Uzbek]]{{·}}[[Tajik language|Tajik]]{{·}}[[Russian language|Russian]] |religions = [[Islam]] |related = }}
'''Uzbek Canadians''' are Canadian citizens of [[Uzbek people|Uzbek]] descent or persons of Uzbek descent residing in [[Canada]]. According to the [[Canada 2011 Census|2011 Census]] there were 2,725 Canadians who claimed Uzbek ancestry.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/nhs-enm/2011/dp-pd/dt-td/Rp-eng.cfm?TABID=2&LANG=E&APATH=3&DETAIL=0&DIM=0&FL=A&FREE=0&GC=0&GID=1118296&GK=0&GRP=0&PID=105396&PRID=0&PTYPE=105277&S=0&SHOWALL=0&SUB=0&Temporal=2013&THEME=95&VID=0&VNAMEE=&VNAMEF=&D1=0&D2=0&D3=0&D4=0&D5=0&D6=0 |title=2011 National Household Survey: Data tables |author=[[Statistics Canada]] |accessdate=11 February 2014}}</ref> There is a small group of Uzbeks in the city of [[Guelph]]. There are 150 ethnic Uzbek families from Afghanistan. The Uzbeks of Guelph are mainly coming from Fariab oblast and Andha city in particular.<ref>[http://enews.fergananews.com/news.php?id=1375 Uzbeks in Canada celebrated Uraza bairam (photo)]</ref>
==Notable Uzbek Canadians== * [[Artour "Arteezy" Babaev]], professional ''Dota'' player
